{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"28653bb5-f01b-47b5-a562-63963be152d5","content":"Use `Assert.ThrowsException` (MSTest) or `Assert.Throws` (xUnit/NUnit) instead:\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void CreateUser_NullEmail_ThrowsException()\n{\n    var service = new UserService();\n\n    var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(\n        () => service.CreateUser(null, \"John\"));\n\n    Assert.AreEqual(\"email\", ex.ParamName); // bonus: verify details\n}\n```\n\n**Why switch:**\n- `[ExpectedException]` passes if *any* line throws — it can't pinpoint the source, masking bugs in arrange/setup code.\n- `Assert.ThrowsException` scopes the assertion to the exact call and lets you inspect the exception (message, inner exception, etc.).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f0d3784d-a578-4341-add8-c2919e4e78a6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about modernizing a C# test that uses the `[ExpectedException]` attribute. This is a general knowledge question - no need to explore the codebase.","outputTokens":250,"requestId":"4C11:2BC959:B75EF7:E4F1FD:6A013091"},"id":"e1d08f43-48b4-4d19-a432-f3f96241e2be","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:27:51.989Z","parentId":"e4c4beb7-0249-45f6-b309-0cf14a3884d8"}
